b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":434,"category_name":"Updates","pr_category_id":"2","title_name":"Version Update [Addendum]","message":"<div>Update 1.7.1 is now available for download.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>You may install it right now; otherwise, an automatic update will occur at approximately <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556258400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Note: When you update to version 1.7.1 and play co-op, you will no longer be matched with players using earlier versions of the game. Rooms created by players playing earlier versions will not display in the Room List, and you will not be able to join them using Find a Room. Additionally, if you input an ID using Enter an ID, the room will display, but you will not be able to enter it.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>To commemorate the update, we&rsquo;ll be sending all players a Tenfold Summon Voucher.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>This notice will be modified after they&rsquo;ve been distributed.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><br><\/div><div><strong>\\u25a0Update Details<\/strong><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbChanges to how summoning works and how wyrmprints are acquired:<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>After the maintenance starting <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556247600\\"><\/span>, wyrmprints will no longer appear when summoning. Going forward, you will be able to acquire wyrmprints in quests or by trading for them in the Shop using eldwater.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>We have also changed the amount of wyrmite or diamantium required to 120 for a single summon and 1,200 for a tenfold summon.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>For more information, see the Regarding Changes to Summoning notification and the Regarding Changes to the Amount of Diamantium and Wyrmite Used in Summoning notification.<\/div><div><a href=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.com\/en\/news\/detail\/394\\">Regarding Changes to Summoning notification<\/a><\/div><div><a href=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.com\/en\/news\/detail\/426\\">Regarding Changes to the Amount of Diamantium and Wyrmite Used in Summoning notification<\/a><\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556172000\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><\/div><div>\\u30fbNew event type, defensive battles:<\/div><div>This is a new type of event available for a limited time as a part of the Fire Emblem: Lost Heroes event, which starts after the maintenance starting <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556247600\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Protect the gate from the attacking Dyrenell Empire troops!<\/div><div>For more information, see the notification A New Event, Fire Emblem: Lost Heroes, Is Now Live!<\/div><div><a href=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.com\/en\/news\/detail\/427\\">A New Event, Fire Emblem: Lost Heroes, Is Now Live!<\/a><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAI adjustments for allies on your team and adventurers during Auto play:<\/div><div>We have made it so that the AI for allies on your team and adventurers playing with Auto enabled will use Force Strike. We&#39;ve also made other adjustments to help the AI attack enemies more proactively.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAdditional co-op features:<\/div><div>It is now possible to set an Objective in Create a Room with Conditions.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/2cdf5a201588a2aa131f996a8a42b7f3.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>You can select from Up for Anything, Earn Epithets, Clear Quest Endeavors, Repeat a Quest, and Seek Help.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>[Update <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556456400\\"><\/span>]<\/div><div>Note: With the exception of Up for Anything, players who select Quick Play will not be able to enter rooms with a set Objective.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>We have also added a Room List button to the co-op screen for each quest.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/f57a4ea6f31827c58eaa5c1b8598fa49.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>This will show a list of rooms with openings for the quest you selected.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The Room List screen will now display rooms with conditions, and you will be able to check the conditions set for each room.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>In addition to checking whether you meet the conditions, you will also be able to see condition trends. Also, the background displayed behind your team in the room will now show the equipped dragon instead of the adventurer. This will make it easier to tell what dragons the other players have equipped.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/59c9fcd328929f35d3404da63a055ea9.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Along with the addition of these co-op features, after the maintenance starting <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556247600\\"><\/span>, we will be resetting the number of times you can earn the Social Reward by playing co-op with a new player for the first time.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>After clearing a quest you can earn 50 wyrmite per player (up to a maximum of 50 players), so be sure to check out the new co-op features!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAbility levels for wyrmprints:<\/div><div>When unbound a second time, the illustration will change and any abilities will be upgraded. When unbound a fourth time, any abilities will be upgraded even further.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Note: This will be applied after the maintenance starting <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556247600\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAttacking enemies who are knocked down:<\/div><div>It is now possible to damage enemies who have been knocked down.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbWyrmprint list-display feature added:<\/div><div>We have added a Switch View button to enable switching to a list display for wyrmprints.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/9712c4d1ebf4d577fecfc7e33002db8c.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAdditional teams:<\/div><div>We have increased the number of teams you can have from six to nine.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbSticker changes:<\/div><div>We have changed the following stickers.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/1ebc599c8b3243e7f117d0f528269058.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Note: This will be applied after the maintenance starting <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556247600\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><br><\/div><div><strong>\\u25a0Regarding Trading Wyrmprints in the Shop<\/strong><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>After the maintenance starting <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556247600\\"><\/span>, it will be possible to trade eldwater for wyrmprints in the Shop.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbTreasure Trade for wyrmprints:<\/div><div>We&rsquo;ve added a new Wyrmprints button to the Shop.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/6e38361a02ea09246138ef87f494f7c2.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The wyrmprint lineup will be split into the following tabs.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbFeatured<\/div><div>\\u30fb5\\u2605<\/div><div>\\u30fb4\\u2605<\/div><div>\\u30fb3\\u2605<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The Featured tab will contain newly-added wyrmprints and wyrmprints available for trade for a limited time.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Checking copies held:<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbYou can tap the copies-held magnifying-glass icon in the top right to check how many of the selected wyrmprint you have.<\/div><div>\\u30fbYou can check how many copies you have and what level of unbound they are.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/19f52ecd1ffaefe9ba89a0da0fe7678c.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Fully Unbound button:<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbWith the Fully Unbound button added to the bottom left, you can check the abilities of the wyrmprint when fully unbound.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><br><\/div><div><strong>\\u25a0Other Changes<\/strong><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAdventurers will no longer turn around when damaged.<\/div><div>Note: When knocked back, adventurers will face the direction of the damage they received.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe &ldquo;Don&#39;t allow any of your team to fall in battle&quot; completion reward will now only apply to your own party in raid-event boss battles.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe animations on several screens have been shortened to raise the overall pace of the game.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIt is now clearer when you have reached the exchange limit for an item in the Treasure Trade in the Shop.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Treasure Trade UI in the Shop has been adjusted to make it clearer what you are trading for.<\/div><div>\\u30fbA Schedule button has been added to the quest-selection screen for Void Battles.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWeapon abilities have been added to the sort conditions on the weapon-list screen and the weapon-crafting screen.<\/div><div>\\u30fbTapping Close after enhancing a weapon now returns you to the Enhance tab.<\/div><div>\\u30fbTapping Cancel after upgrading a weapon to maximum level now returns you to the upgrade screen for that weapon.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe order of each summon has been changed on the summon screen.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe effects of abilities which are conditional based on HP have been applied to the stats display on the edit-team screen and the details screen.<\/div><div>Note: Only effects that trigger when at 100% HP will be applied. This is merely a display change. It will not increase Might.<\/div><div>\\u30fbOther small UI adjustments were made on several screens.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556258400\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><\/div><div>\\u30fbA 1,230 diamantium option has been added to the Shop.<\/div><div>\\u30fbAn Updated mark has been added to the list of updated notifications.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><br><\/div><div><strong>\\u25a0Balance Adjustments &nbsp;<\/strong><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Update <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556258400\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><\/div><div>The following balance adjustments will be applied <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556258400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbQuests like those in the main campaign will now drop wyrmprints with 3\\u2605 rarity and higher which formerly appeared in summoning. See the details screen of each quest for more information.<\/div><div>\\u30fbConsidering the increased opportunity for crafting weapons due to the addition of Void Battles, we&rsquo;ve increased the amount of weapons you can have by 100.<\/div><div>\\u30fbDue to the overall increase of playable contents, we have reduced the number of daily bonuses for Avenue to Power, Avenue to Fortune, Elemental Ruins, Dragon Trials and Imperial Onslaught by 1 each, and have increased the rewards from each daily bonus accordingly.<\/div><div>Note: The amount of rewards dropped from each quest has not been modified.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIncreased the potency of co-ability effects for 3\\u2605 and 4\\u2605 adventurers, making the effect match those of 5\\u2605 adventurers when fully upgraded.<\/div><div>\\u30fbElemental scales have been removed from the materials required to obtain skills on the second mana circle and to unbind the third mana circle.<\/div><div>Note: As part of the adjustment described above, we will be sending elemental scales to players who used them in the applicable areas before the maintenance starting at <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556247600\\"><\/span>, starting after the maintenance ends.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe potency of wyrmprint abilities has been increased overall.<\/div><div>Note: The post-adjustment stats will be applied to your team&#39;s Might when you adjust the team on the team screen.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Might of the High Midgardsormr Res ability on Glorious Tempest has been adjusted.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe maximum value for the following wyrmprint abilities has been raised.<\/div><div><br><\/div><table style=\\"width: 100%;\\"><tbody><tr><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">Skill Damage<br><\/td><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">35% &rarr; 40%<br><\/td><\/tr><tr><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">Strength<br><\/td><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">15% &rarr; 20%<br><\/td><\/tr><tr><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">Force Strike<br><\/td><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">40% &rarr; 50%<br><\/td><\/tr><tr><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">Broken Punisher<br><\/td><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">25% &rarr; 30%<br><\/td><\/tr><tr><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">Gauge Accelerator<br><\/td><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">30% &rarr; 35%<br><\/td><\/tr><tr><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">Shield Prep<br><\/td><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">II(20%) &rarr; III(30%)<br><\/td><\/tr><tr><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">Burning Punisher<br><\/td><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">25% &rarr; 30%<br><\/td><\/tr><tr><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">Dragon Time<br><\/td><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">15% &rarr; 20%<br><\/td><\/tr><tr><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">Slayer&#39;s Strength<br><\/td><td style=\\"width: 50.0000%;\\">5% &rarr; 6%<br><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbThe final wave of Avenue to Power has been adjusted to include a boss.<\/div><div>Note: Other than the addition of wyrmprints as drop rewards starting with this version, there will be no other changes to the obtainable rewards.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe &quot;Defeat all the enemies&quot; clear condition for Ch. 6 \/ 1-2, Watch for Falling Trees (Hard) has been changed to &quot;Eliminate a specific threat.&quot;<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe descriptions for some items have been adjusted.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe HP and Strength of all the 3\\u2605 characters and of the following 4\\u2605 characters have been increased:<\/div><div>The Prince, Elisanne, Ranzal, Cleo, Luca, Celliera, Melsa, Elias, Botan, Su Fang, Felicia, Alex.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><strong>\\u25a0Issues Fixed<\/strong><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The following issues have been fixed in this version:<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen Ku Hai performed Force Strike after using the Keen Blade skill, enemy collision no longer applied.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen Albert performed Force Strike after using the Thunderous Impulse skill, enemy collision no longer applied.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen receiving trap damage while midair as part of a sword attack, the attack was canceled.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen Julietta used the Glorious Guard skill, certain attacks hit more while under its effects.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Dragon Gauge did not fill when additional damage was dealt to enemies due to bleeding, burning, or poison.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIt was sometimes impossible to progress on the enhance screen after performing certain steps.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThere was a delay before the ready mark displayed after tapping Ready in co-op.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen normal image quality was set on certain devices and the number of goodies in the goodie box was 100 or more between both Limited and No Limit, it displayed as 9.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen unbinding on certain devices, weapons and dragons in the unbind materials did not display, so it only showed item materials.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIn Helper Settings, it was not possible to change wyrmprints when filtered using Sort.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen moving from the unbind screen to the Castle, the unbind screen&rsquo;s display remained in the top-left of the screen.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIn High Mercury&#39;s Trial, under certain conditions it was sometimes possible to avoid attacks which should be unavoidable without entering the Spheres of Salvation.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556258400\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen certain buffs overlapped and the first buff ended, the second buff also ended.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe effect at the start of the quest, icon, and text above the adventurer&#39;s head did not display properly for the The Petal Queen wyrmprint.<\/div><div>\\u30fbOn certain devices the game&rsquo;s icon sometimes displayed as white on the device&rsquo;s home screen.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Note:<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>It may take time for the store to reflect the updated information. Players may not be able to perform updates due to their device&rsquo;s data cache being full. If you are unable to perform the update, restart your device, and then try downloading it from the store.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556258400\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><\/div><div>As a token of our appreciation, the following item has been sent to players who started playing before <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556247600\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbTenfold Summon Voucher x1<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>For players who log in before <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1556863199\\"><\/span>, this gift can be claimed from your goodie box for up to seven days after logging in.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div>","start_time":1556161200,"prev_article_id":"266","next_article_id":"480","image_path":"","update_time":1556457016}}}'